              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "For normalization the 6Li yield at 7.0 MeV and 25 degr.",
                "was compared with the 9Be(He3,t)9B yield at 7.0 MeV",
                "and90 degr. and with the 9Be(p,alpha)6Li yield at",
                "4.0 MeV and 90 degr. This procedure provided two",
                "independent determinations of the product of the",
                "spectrometer solid angle and the number of 9Be atoms",
                "in the target. These two dimensions were in agreement",
                "within experimental error, and their weighted average",
                "was used to obtain the 9Be(3He,6Li)6Li absolute cross",
                "section."
              ]
            }
          ],
